records.addlTxt:
02:05 PM Defendant Austin R. Figueroa in court, appearing by video from in custody in Barron County Jail, with attorney Stephanie E Thomas-Schmidt, appearing by video.  Bruce Robert Poquette appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Court calls case and recites appearances.  Court has discussion DEF on zoom appearance.  Court reviews case.  Atty Thomas-Schmidt has received revocation packet and no corrections are needed.  State has received revocation packet.  Court indicates DEF is here for sentencing in Sawyer County case 15CF56.  State makes statement, reviews cases from other counties, and argues sentencing.  State makes recommendation - 8 years WI prison system - 4 years of confinement + 4 years extended supervision, consecutive to Rusk County 18CF160, with any financial obligations continuing.  State further indicates victims rights compliance.  Court states victim rights have been complied with.  Atty Thomas-Schmidt argues sentencing, requesting 4 years WI prison system - 2 years confinement + 2 years extended supervision, concurrent to Rusk County 18CF160, noting Barron County charges have been resolved (20CF220).  Atty Thomas-Schmidt indicates 292 days credit.  State indicates different calculations for days of credit (120 if consecutive or 283 if concurrent).  DEF addresses Court. Court addresses DEF.  Court clarifies recommendation with State and recommendation and prior sentencing with Atty Thomas-Schmidt.  Court issues sentence.  Court has discussion with all parties on days of credit if consecutive sentence.  State has nothing further.  Atty Thomas-Schmidt has nothing further.  Court indicates WEDS will be completed.  

COURT:  4 years WI Prison system - 2 years initial confinement + 2 years extended supervision, consecutive to Rusk County #18CF160 and Barron County #20CF220.  120 days credit.  Not eligible for ERP, CSP, or Challenge.
